Content:: One-day races and Classics Jan Tratnik (born 23 February 1990 in Ljubljana) is a Slovenian cyclist, who currently rides for UCI WorldTeam Team Bahrain Victorious.[4] He was named in the startlist for the 2017 Giro d'Italia.[5] In July 2019, he was named in the startlist for the 2019 Tour de France.[6]
